<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Aetna Posts Record Loss: Aetna Life & Casualty Co. reported its biggest 
quarterly loss in company history, after taking a $1.03-billion charge to cut 
4,000 jobs and drop two product lines. The nation's fourth-largest insurer said 
its fourth-quarter loss was widened to $1.13 billion, or $10.09 a share, from a 
loss of $191.9 million, or $1.74, a year earlier. Core earnings before the 
charge and investment gains jumped to $142.9 million from $600,000, benefiting 
from lower expenses and fewer catastrophe losses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
