<P>
EARTHQUAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * We made a lot of new friends because of the earthquake. There's Tracy and 
Nick, who have lived two doors down from us for 18 months whose names we 
finally learned.And Nick, who came to film the damage to our apartment and 
admired our Christo umbrella prints, which led to a nice conversation. And Tom, 
who has been delivering our pizzas for years, worked side by side with us and 
many others moving out of a damaged building. And countless others whose names 
we never learned, but whose faces we will always remember. Before the 
earthquake we were too busy for passing conversations; now we don't let an 
opportunity pass.  
