<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSBITES: SOME SPECIAL CHOICES FOR VALENTINE'S DINING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNE MICHAUD, Anne Michaud is a staff writer for The Times Orange County 
Edition. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dozens of Orange County restaurants are offering Valentine's Day specials on 
Monday. Here are some of the most interesting: 
</P>
<P>
 Amici Trattoria Enoteca is serving a special prix fixe menu for "Romeo and 
Giulietta." Garden salad or soup, pasta, a choice of veal chop with fontina 
cheese in marsala wine or lobster over fettuccine in a creamy sherry sauce, and 
dessert. The cost is $23.95 per person, plus tax and tip. Dinner will be served 
from 6 to 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 655 Anton Blvd., Costa Mesa. (714) 850-9399. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Garden Bistro, a Mediterranean-style restaurant, will host band Blue Jazz 
for lunch and dinner and distribute long-stem red roses to its female 
customers. 
</P>
<P>
 Lunch, which is $18.95 per person, plus tax and tip, includes salad with fresh 
mint and feta cheese, a choice of entree (salmon, chicken or pasta) and a 
strawberry crepe with chocolate sauce. 
</P>
<P>
 Dinner offers the same salad and dessert, with a choice of lobster ravioli or 
tenderloin lamb chops. The price is $24.95 per person, plus tax and tip. 
</P>
<P>
 Lunch is served 11 a.m. to 3 p.m.; dinner, 6 to 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Crystal Court, second floor, 3333 Bear St., Costa Mesa. (714) 546-6004. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 DaVinci Ristorante is serving "sherbet Eros" and "swordfish Adonis" on its 
Valentine's Day menu. The multi-course dinner is $47 per person, plus tax and 
tip, and includes other dishes: gnocchi Romeo, salmon Valentino, veal scallop 
Aphrodite, strawberries Juliette and cappuccino Cupid. The last is touted as 
"the nectar of love." Dinner is served from 5 to 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 2222 E. 1st St., Santa Ana. (714) 285-1130. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Wine Club in Santa Ana is selling roses throughout the weekend and on 
Monday for $6 a dozen with a purchase of wine or champagne. 
</P>
<P>
 2110 E. McFadden St. (714) 835-6485. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Silky Sullivan's Restaurant & Irish Pub will take a photo of you and your 
sweetheart when you order the special dinner menu on Valentine's Day. For 
$9.95, plus tax and tip, diners can choose from among three entrees: prime rib, 
chicken with bacon in a brandy brown sauce, or red snapper. Dinners, served 
until 1 a.m., include soup or salad bar, garlic bread and Irish-style potatoes, 
rice pilaf or baked potato. 
</P>
<P>
 Silky's is also throwing in a free rose. 
</P>
<P>
 10201 Slater Ave., Fountain Valley. (714) 963-2718. 
</P>
<P>
