<HEADLINE>
<P>
DO IT!: RAIN OR SHINE, THIS RUN IS AN ADVENTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICK VANDERKNYFF, Rick VanderKnyff is a free-lance writer who regularly 
contributes to The Times Orange County Edition. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On the morning of last year's Great American Adventure Run at Central Park in 
Huntington Beach, Oscar J. Rosales woke up to what would normally be a race 
director's nightmare: rain, lots of it. 
</P>
<P>
 "It poured bloody murder," Rosales recalled in a phone interview. But the 
runners didn't seem to mind. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have more people telling me this year, 'Gosh, I hope it rains again.' " 
</P>
<P>
 The race returns Saturday. The event, with courses of 2.8 and 4.8 miles, 
attracted 350 runners, about what Rosales would have expected on a sunny day. 
Rosales attributes that to the hardiness of the people attracted to his events, 
which eschew the streets for a lush park setting and courses that include dirt 
and grass as well as asphalt pathways. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's nothing like a road race. It's totally rural and cross-country," Rosales 
said, adding that first-timers to his Central Park events -- which include the 
Hillsea in May and the Sunset in the Park in September -- are often surprised 
at how different the experience is from road races. 
</P>
<P>
 The 2.8-mile event begins at 8 a.m.; the 4.8-mile run starts at 8:30 a.m. 
Runners who enter both events are eligible for special plaques, in addition to 
the regular awards for age-group winners in each individual race. 
</P>
<P>
 Records for the 2.8-mile course are 14 minutes, 36 seconds, by Matt Messner 
for the men and 16:37 by Beth Metcalf for the women. Metcalf also holds the 
women's record for the 4.8-mile course, at 28 minutes; Alfredo Rosas holds the 
men's record at 23:27. 
</P>
<P>
 Race-day registration for the event will open at 6:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Also on Saturday, they'll be running off-road deep in the Cleveland National 
Forest, in the latest edition of the Winter Trail Run Series. The 22-kilometer 
race begins, as all the events do, at Blue Jay Campground (five miles north of 
El Cariso Village off Ortega Highway, 22 miles east of San Juan Capistrano). 
</P>
<P>
 The run begins at 8 a.m. Race-day entry price is $23. Future events include a 
12K on Feb. 26 ($12) and a 50K run on March 26 ($40). For information, call Baz 
Hawley at (714) 380-2666. 
</P>
<P>
 What: Great American Adventure Run. 
</P>
<P>
 When: Saturday, Feb. 12, at 8 a.m. for the 2.8-mile run and at 8:30 a.m. for 
4.8-mile event (registration opens at 6:30 a.m.) 
</P>
<P>
 Where: Huntington Central Park, Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Whereabouts: From the San Diego (405) Freeway, exit at Warner Avenue and head 
east. Turn left on Edwards Street, and left again on Central Park Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Wherewithal: $17 (includes T-shirt). 
</P>
<P>
 Where to call: (714) 841-5417. 
</P>
</TEXT>
