<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; ARKANSAS ENDS KENTUCKY WINNING STREAK, 90-82 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Arkansas played bookends to a Kentucky winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
 When Wednesday's game began, the third-ranked Razorbacks had been the last 
visitor to win at Rupp Arena in Lexington, Ky., on Jan. 25, 1992. When it 
ended, Arkansas, 17-2 and 7-2 in the Southeastern Conference, had closed the 
winning streak at 33, defeating the fourth-ranked Wildcats, 90-82. 
</P>
<P>
 Scotty Thurman finished with 26 points and Corliss Williamson added 21 for 
Arkansas in a game that had Kentucky Coach Rick Pitino both hospitable and ill. 
</P>
<P>
 "My congratulations go to Arkansas," Pitino said. "They've done this to us 
twice in a row. They've been the superior basketball team twice in a row." 
</P>
<P>
 But "it's such a farce," he said of his team's performance. "I feel like 
throwing up." 
</P>
<P>
 A 19-3 run by the Razorbacks midway through the second half put them in front 
for good, though their lead was often tenuous. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 6 Connecticut 94, Boston College 91 -- Donyell Marshall scored 33 points, 
including the last four points of the second overtime for the Huskies (20-2, 
10-1) in a Big East game at Newton, Mass. Boston College (16-7, 7-5) pulled 
within 91-90, but Marshall hit a basket 20 seconds later to clinch the game. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 10 Purdue 98, Northwestern 81 -- It took Glenn Robinson less than nine 
minutes to reach his 44th consecutive double-figure scoring game, and he had 22 
points in the first half to spark the Boilermakers (19-3, 7-3) past 
Northwestern (9-9, 0-9) in a Big Ten game at West Lafayette, Ind. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 15 Missouri 82, Colorado 70 -- Melvin Booker and Kelly Thames cooled off 
the Buffaloes (10-10, 2-6) in the second half with two free throws and a 
three-pointer, and freshman Kelly Thames scored 20 points to lead the Tigers 
(17-2, 8-0) in a Big Eight game at Columbia, Mo. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 17 St. Louis 90, Iowa State 75 -- Scott Highmark scored 23 points and the 
Billikens (19-1) hit 12 three-pointers in beating Iowa State (11-8) at St. 
Louis. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 19 Alabama Birmingham 78, DePaul 73 -- Robert Shannon scored 22 points, 
including the go-ahead basket with 45 seconds to go, and the Blazers (18-3, 
6-2) withstood a strong second-half rally by DePaul (13-7, 2-6) in a Great 
Midwest game at Rosemont, Ill. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 20 Florida 74, Mississippi 55 -- Craig Brown had 21 points, 13 rebounds 
and six assists as the Gators (19-3, 9-1) beat Ole Miss (11-8, 4-5) in an SEC 
game Oxford, Miss. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 21 Wisconsin 77, Penn State 64 -- Rashard Griffith returned from a 
two-game absence because of a knee injury and scored 15 points to help the 
Badgers (15-4, 6-4 to a Big Ten victory at Madison, Wis., where they are 12-0. 
John Amaechi scored 18 points to lead Penn State (10-9, 3-7). 
</P>
<P>
 No. 23 Minnesota 79, Ohio State 73 -- Voshon Lenard scored 24 points and the 
Gophers (16-7, 6-4) shot 75% in the second half to beat the Buckeyes (10-11, 
3-7) in a Big Ten game in Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 24 Illinois 72, Michigan State 64 -- Deon Thomas scored 25 points to lead 
the Illini (13-5, 6-3) to a Big Ten victory at Champaign, Ill. The Spartans 
(14-9, 5-6) were outscored, 22-7, from the free-throw line. OTHER GAMES 
</P>
<P>
 Todd Fuller scored 14 points as North Carolina State (8-13, 3-7) won, 67-54, 
over Virginia (12-7, 6-4) in an ACC game at Raleigh, N.C. . . . Jamie Watson 
had 13 of his 20 points in the second half and South Carolina (6-13) made a 
school-record 14 three-pointers to win, 91-88, at Clemson (12-10). . . . Guard 
B.J. Tyler scored 18 points for Texas (15-6, 7-1) in a 94-66 Southwest 
Conference victory over Southern Methodist (3-16, 1-7). 
</P>
