<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SOCCER ROUNDUP; NEWPORT HARBOR MANAGES TO TIE TOP-RANKED CORONA DEL MAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newport Harbor tied top-ranked Corona del Mar, 1-1, in a Sea View League boys' 
soccer game Wednesday at Corona del Mar High. 
</P>
<P>
 Todd McIlwain scored the tying goal early in the second half for the unranked 
Sailors (5-12-5, 3-8-2). Sailor goalkeeper Steve Kleha had 13 saves. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Boyce scored the goal for the Sea Kings (18-2-4, 11-0-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In other Sea View League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback 2, Santa Margarita 1 -- John Maldonado and Raul Montes scored for 
third-ranked Saddleback (17-3-3, 8-1-3). Seventh-ranked Santa Margarita is 
13-4-4, 6-4-2. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 2, Woodbridge 1 -- Alex Seoane scored in the 25th minute of the second 
half to give Tustin the go-ahead goal. Tye Irwin made eight saves for the 
Tillers (11-8-2, 6-5-2). Gustav Gratzer scored for Woodbridge (4-6-3 in 
league). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 3, Villa Park 0 -- Clay Kilbarger, Sasha Saneff and Todd Stearman 
scored for eighth-ranked Canyon (16-5-4, 6-2-2). Goalie Aaron Harries had 10 
saves for the Comanches, who finished first in league. 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 2, El Modena 0 -- Steve Patterson scored two unassisted goals for 
Foothill (7-7-7, 3-3-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado 2, Loara 1 -- Brian Hurley, back after missing three games with a 
knee injury, scored the game-winner with four minutes remaining for El Dorado 
(9-6-6, 4-3-2). Kevin Haynes scored the other Hawks' goal. Kevin Johnson scored 
for Loara. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza 2, Los Alamitos 2 -- Esperanza (13-5-5, 5-1-3) missed a chance to 
clinch a league title, but still can do so with a victory or tie Friday against 
Loara. Jake Thomas and David Clemmins scored for the Aztecs. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
 Sunny Hills 2, Troy 0 -- Sunny Hills (14-5-3, 7-1-1) remained tied for the 
league lead with Sonora after shutting out host Troy. D.J. Buckley scored his 
16th goal for the Lancers. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 1, Trabuco Hills 0 -- R.B. Edwards scored on a throw-in from Kyle 
Brown in the 17th minute of the second half, as Laguna Hills (11-9-1, 7-2) 
moved into a tie with Trabuco Hills (7-2) with one game remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 In the South Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Dana Hills 1, Capistrano Valley 1 -- Capistrano Valley's Chris Tullar scored 
in the second half to tie Dana Hills (11-8-1, 1-6-2) and keep the Cougars 
(12-5-5, 4-2-3) within a game of first-place Mater Dei. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 5, Mission Viejo 0 -- John Gerdis scored two goals and Kevin 
Quigley, Mike McCabe and Olivier Rossi each scored one for Mater Dei (19-1-4, 
6-1-2), which clinched at least a tie for the league championship. Mission 
Viejo is 3-13-4, 2-5-2. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro 2, San Clemente 1 -- Brent Stringham and Jose Lopez each scored for 
sixth-ranked El Toro (5-3-1 in league). Troy Wenger scored for San Clemente 
(7-9-7, 1-3-5). 
</P>
