<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CYPRESS GIVES COACH JOHNSON A GOING-AWAY GIFT BY 
UPSETTING SADDLEBACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jim Falletta made a six-foot baseline jumper with two seconds left to give 
host Cypress a 64-62 upset of first-place Saddleback in an Orange Empire 
Conference men's basketball game. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory came a day after Cypress Coach Don Johnson announced his 
retirement, effective at the end of the season. Johnson is California's 
winningest community college men's basketball coach. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cypress victory ended Saddleback's eight-game conference winning streak 
and dropped the Gauchos into a first-place tie with Riverside with three games 
left. Saddleback (19-7, 9-2) plays host to Golden West and Orange Coast is at 
Riverside Friday.  
</P>
<P>
 Craig Olson had 15 points and Matt Kennedy added 14 for Cypress (13-17, 4-7).  
</P>
<P>
 In other Orange Empire Conference men's games: 
</P>
<P>
 Riverside 98, Fullerton 76 -- Ronald Kenan had 25 points for host Riverside 
(23-6, 9-2). Tyrone Merriweather scored 16 for Fullerton (21-9, 6-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast 88, Golden West 81 -- Derek Roche had 26 points host OCC (13-13, 
3-8), which has won two consecutive games after losing seven in a row.  
</P>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago 98, Irvine Valley 93 -- Sean Amos scored 30 points for 
visiting Rancho Santiago (19-9, 7-4).  
</P>
<P>
 In Orange Empire Conference women's games: 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West 65, Orange Coast 55 -- Julie Murdent scored 22 points and added 17 
rebounds as host Golden West (27-4, 9-1) clinched a tie for its fifth 
consecutive conference title. It was also the 66th consecutive home victory for 
Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
 OCC's Flo Luppani made a pair of three-pointers to cut Golden West's lead to 
47-46 with 8:02 left but the Rustlers scored the next six points. Orange Coast 
got as close as four, 56-52, with 1:32 left but Kristin Brun made four free 
throws in the next minute to keep the lead safe. 
</P>
<P>
 LeAnn Kazmer had 16 points and America Robledo added 11 for Orange Coast 
(17-11, 5-4). STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
