<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JASON REID 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 San Clemente football Coach Mark McElroy, hospitalized after experiencing 
chest pains at school Tuesday, was released from Samaritan Medical Center-San 
Clemente Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Doctors are unsure what caused his pain but said McElroy, 33, did not suffer a 
heart attack, McElroy said from home Wednesday.He said his pain subsided late 
Tuesday, but doctors decided to have him stay overnight for observation and 
additional tests. 
</P>
<P>
 McElroy is taking medication and must return to the hospital Friday for more 
testing. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've been better," McElroy said. "Hopefully (the doctors) will have a better 
idea of what's going on (after Friday)." 
</P>
<P>
 McElroy, who began complaining of pain Tuesday morning, said he does not 
expect to resume his duties at San Clemente this week. JASON REID 
</P>
</TEXT>
