<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fred Di Palma of Savanna and George Pascoe of Huntington Beach have been 
selected coaches for the 35th Orange County North-South All-Star Football Game, 
which is scheduled July 8 at Orange Coast College's LeBard Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Di Palma will coach the North and Pascoe the South for the game, sponsored by 
the Orange County Youth Foundation.The South roster will be announced April 9 
and the North's on April 16. 
</P>
<P>
 Di Palma led Savanna to the Southern Section Division VI title. Huntington 
Beach finished 13-1 under Pascoe, losing to Los Alamitos in the Division II 
championship game. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress High has named Don Turnbull boys' track and field coach, replacing Ray 
Fenton. 
</P>
<P>
 Turnbull, a 1986 Cypress graduate, returns for his second tour of duty with 
the Centurions; he coached cross-country from 1988-1990. Turnbull most recently 
was cross-country and track coach at La Quinta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
