</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UC Irvine men's tennis team, ranked 25th in the nation, swept three 
doubles matches to gain one team point and defeat Arizona, 4-3, in a 
nonconference match Wednesday at the UCI Tennis Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Julian Foxon, Luke Fitzsimons and Carlos Bustos each won in singles as UCI 
gained a split of six matches.Foxon and Fitzsimons remain unbeaten in singles. 
The Anteaters are 3-1; the Wildcats, ranked 37th, are 1-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Freshman Marc-Andre Tardif, who teamed with Bustos to win at No. 2 doubles, 
was bothered by a shoulder injury suffered in New Mexico last weekend and did 
not play singles. Tardif is ranked 47th nationally in singles. 
