<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; COUNCIL TO 
SET UP PANEL TO IMPROVE RACE RELATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Acknowledging the city's ethnic diversity and the tensions that stem from it, 
the Los Angeles City Council has voted to expand its Human Relations Commission 
and set up a special committee to study ways of improving race relations. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Mark Ridley-Thomas, who proposed the measure, said the blue-ribbon 
committee on race relations will work to highlight the city's diverse 
communities and to prevent conflicts. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridley-Thomas called the city's existing Human Relations Commission woefully 
inadequate, noting that it has only two full-time staffers and a budget of 
$100,000. 
</P>
