</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A mistrial was declared this week in the excessive-force trial of two former 
Baldwin Park police officers after a Los Angles Superior Court jury failed to 
decide whether the officers beat a burglary suspect during an arrest three 
years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The jury deliberated for 5 1/2 days in the trial of Louis Price, 38, and 
Kenneth Shearen, 29.Thy were accused of beating convicted burglar Gilbert 
Gutierrez on Feb. 11, 1991, after a gas station mini-store was burglarized. 
Jurors voted 6 to 6 to convict Price and 7 to 5 to convict Shearen. 
</P>
<P>
 The former officers, who were dismissed from their jobs for using excessive 
force, return to court Feb. 17. The district attorney's office will seek a 
retrial. But defense attorneys called the case "ludicrous," saying that medical 
evidence did not support the beating allegations. 
</P>
