<HEADLINE>
<P>
LONGTIME HUNTINGTON BEACH EDUCATOR DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marjorie Flanagan, a 45-year resident of Huntington Beach who taught 
elementary school for nearly 20 years, died Saturday after an extended illness. 
She was 67. 
</P>
<P>
 Flanagan taught at Huntington Beach Elementary School and McGaw Intermediate 
School in Seal Beach, retiring in 1976. She was a participant in the American 
Field Service, an organization that sends local students abroad and hosts 
foreign students, and the Huntington Beach Chapter of P.E.O. Sisterhood, a 
philanthropic education organization. 
</P>
<P>
 "She had a very bright mind, was a leader in whatever she did, and her 
students really loved her, I'm sure," said Betty Steidinger, a close friend and 
colleague. 
</P>
<P>
 She is survived by her husband, Scott, a retired superintendent of the 
Huntington Beach High School District; a daughter, Kerry Flanagan, 40, of 
Laguna Beach; a son, Scott Flanagan, 41, of Palos Verdes Estates; and two 
grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
 Services will be private. 
</P>
