<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS; BE WELCOME TOP PICK IN ANAHEIM PACING LEG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ANDERSEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Be Welcome, a 5-year-old Albatross offspring whose 2-, 3- and 4-year-old 
seasons all ended in leg injuries after one race, will be a big favorite 
tonight at Los Alamitos in the 10th race, second elimination of the Anaheim 
Pacing Series. 
</P>
<P>
 After finishing eighth in a nine-horse field on Jan. 8 to open his 5-year-old 
season, Be Welcome has won three of four starts, with a career-best winning 
mile time of 1:56 3/5 Saturday night.In the fourth, on Jan. 29, he finished 
third to You Better Bet, a 5-year-old with $200,000 in winnings in his career. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anaheim Pacing Series is the first of several events designed to give 
horses who are not in the top class a chance to race for bigger purses. It is a 
restricted event for colts and geldings who had not won three races and earned 
more than $5,000 -- $7,500 for California breds -- as of Dec. 31. 
</P>
<P>
 Maxanali, a 3-year-old who will be one of the leading contenders in the first 
division, the seventh race, ended '93 with two victories but had earned more 
than $18,000. Since then, he has won two races and added more than $12,000 to 
his bankroll. 
</P>
<P>
 The first four finishers in each division and the fifth-place horse with the 
faster time will qualify for the final next Thursday. STEVE ANDERSEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
