COLLEGE ROUNDUP; MARTIN FINDS RANGE IN MOORPARK WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sean Martin scored 25 points and had seven assists to lead Moorpark College to 
a 90-71 basketball victory Wednesday over Santa Barbara City in a Western State 
Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
 The host Raiders improved to 21-8, 3-3 in the conference. 
</P>
<P>
 Martin, a sophomore from Agoura High, made five of eight shots from 
three-point range and converted all six of his free throws. Jimmy Harbour, a 
freshman from Camarillo, scored 12 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for the 
Raiders. Paul Foster added 11 points and 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Bakersfield 79, Valley 61 -- The Renegades turned a three-point game into a 
rout with a 51-point second half and pounded Valley (10-17, 2-5) in a WSC game 
at Bakersfield. 
</P>
<P>
 Ten of Valley's 11 players scored, but the Monarchs were no match for the 
Renegades (12-16, 5-1), who shot 63% (17 of 27) from the field in the second 
half. 
</P>
<P>
 Kenyth Henry led Valley with 15 points. WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 62, Cuesta 38 -- Julie Hardy scored 12 of her 20 points in the first 
half, leading the Pirates (22-5, 6-1) to a Western State Conference victory at 
Ventura. The Pirates broke out to a 21-4 lead and put the game away with a 9-0 
run to start the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Cornell scored 18 points for Cuesta (10-12, 3-4). 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons 82, Glendale 62 -- Rebekah Cunnan scored 21 points and Carlisa 
Hamagaki added 20 for the Cougars (15-12, 7-0) in a WSC game. Suzy Woo had 27 
points for Glendale. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 82, Santa Barbara 65 -- Janette Oriza collected 35 points, 17 
rebounds, four steals and four assists for the Raiders, who overcame a 17-point 
first-half deficit in a WSC North Division game. Moorpark's Joy Garcia had 14 
points, including four three-point baskets in the second half, when the Raiders 
outscored the Vaqueros, 47-23. Sara Marroquin added 12 points for Moorpark 
(10-16, 7-6 in conference, 2-5 in division). BASEBALL 
</P>
