<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRESCENTA VALLEY'S HAGMAN SETS 3-POINT MARK FOR SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sarah Hagman of Crescenta Valley High scored 27 points and set a Southern 
Section one-season record for three-point baskets Wednesday, while leading the 
Falcons to a 50-38 victory over Pasadena in a Pacific League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Hagman, who made four three-point baskets against Pasadena, has made 115 this 
season, breaking a record set a season ago by Chino's Amee Pina, who finished 
with 112. 
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley Coach Marc Ward stopped the game in the second quarter when 
Hagman scored her 113th and honored her achievement by handing her the game 
ball. Hagman, who owns the Southern Section mark for most three-pointers in a 
game with 13, scored 12 of her 27 points in the second quarter to fuel the 
Falcons' 28-20 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Falcons (18-5, 8-1 in league play), who clinched a share of the league 
title, tied a section record for three-point baskets.  
</P>
<P>
 Crescenta Valley has made 151 three-pointers this season, equaling the number 
posted by Brea-Olinda in 1991-92. 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Green added 10 points for Crescenta Valley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
