<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / COUNTYWIDE: WORKSHOP ON TRANSIT; GRANTS SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GEOFF BOUCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Caltrans will sponsor a workshop Feb. 25 for local public and private 
nonprofit agencies interested in applying for federal grants for disabled or 
senior citizen transportationservices. 
</P>
<P>
 The Federal Transit Administration has more than $5 million in grants for 
California transit services that serve the two limited-mobility groups.Agencies 
can use the grants to pay for up to 80% of the purchase price for buses, vans 
or other vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
 The program has helped buy 1,500 vehicles statewide since it was created in 
the 1970s, California Department of Transportation officials said. Applications 
can be filed at any district office of Caltrans, the state agency that 
distributes the grants. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop will help prospective applicants understand the grant 
requirements and review process. The workshop will be at 9 a.m. at the Caltrans 
District 12 office at 1700 Carnegie St., Building B, Room 100, in Santa Ana. To 
make reservations, call Barbara Gossett at (714) 724-2732 or Larry Layne at 
(714) 724-2267. GEOFF BOUCHER 
</P>
