<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS / CENTRAL: WESTMINSTER; TET FESTIVAL EXPECTED TO ATTRACT 
100,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As many as 100,000 people are expected to attend the three-day celebration of 
this year's Tet Festival in Little Saigon that begins Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Activities include cultural exhibits, martial arts demonstrations, firecracker 
displays, lion dances, karaoke contests and cultural presentations. The event 
is being sponsored by the Asian American Merchants Assn., a nonprofit group. 
</P>
<P>
 Gates are open from 10 a.m. to 10 p.m. Organizers said part of the proceeds 
will be donated to local nonprofit groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
