CITY REZONES FAIRVIEW-MACARTHUR; AREA TO SPEED CENTER DEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has rezoned 19 acres at Fairview Street and MacArthur 
Boulevard, making the area easier to develop as a community shopping center. 
</P>
<P>
 At its regular meeting Monday, the council approved the plan to rezone the 
vacant land, which is owned by C.J. Segerstrom and Sons. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayor Daniel H. Young said the rezoning would provide an excellent opportunity 
for quick development. 
</P>
<P>
 A report to the council states that no specific development plan has been 
proposed for the site, located on the east side of Fairview between Alton 
Avenue and MacArthur Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 Kenneth Adams, city planning manager, said after the meeting that the prior 
zoning allowed the site to be developed in two parts, one business and one 
residential. A single large commercial development, however, would fare much 
better than a smaller one. 
