Howell identified his client as the defendant. Howell's attorney, David L. Beck 
of Knoxville, Tenn., said all charges against Howell were dismissed because of 
insufficient evidence. 
</P>
<P>
 Howell had been charged with lying and obstructing justice during the Tailhook 
probe. He was also charged with assaulting a Tailhook investigator and with 
spending a night during the convention at the Las Vegas Hilton with a woman 
other than his wife. 
</P>
<P>
 Pentagon investigators concluded that 83 women were assaulted or molested at 
the convention. Many of the women were molested on the hotel's third floor, 
where men lined the hallway and grabbed women as they tried to pass. 
