EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; 2 ON AIRPORT PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents of Van Nuys and Sherman Oaks were appointed by Los Angeles City 
Councilman Zev Yaroslavsky to a Van Nuys Airport citizens advisory panel. 
</P>
<P>
 Yaroslavsky announced Wednesday the appointment of Candace Campbell, a Van 
Nuys resident who helps operate a consulting and training business, and Doron 
Kauper, a Sherman Oaks film producer and chairman of a group dedicated to 
reducing airport noise. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys Airport Citizens meets each month to advise the city's Board of 
Airport Commissioners on contracts, development projects and other issues at 
the airport. HUGO MARTIN 
