<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN ARRESTED IN FATAL STABBING OF WOMAN, 89 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 89-year-old woman was found stabbed to death and a suspect has been 
arrested in the killing, police reported Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Josephine Adinolfi was found dead in her home at 707 Salem St. on Tuesday 
afternoon of multiple stab wounds, said the Los Angeles County coroner's 
office. 
</P>
<P>
 David Condry, 30, of Glendale was arrested in the slaying. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the first homicide of the year in Glendale, which last year had nine 
killings -- the most in its history. 
</P>
