<P>
 IRS Offers Chance to Settle Disputed Claims: The Internal Revenue Service 
announced that it is offering about 1,500 taxpayers -- mostly large 
corporations -- a chance to settle billions of dollars worth of disputed tax 
claims involving write-offs for intangible assets such as mailing lists and 
computer software. The issue is of enormous importance to businesses that have 
bought other businesses. Since the mid-1980s, the IRS has disallowed more than 
$14.5 billion in claims by these businesses, touching off a torrent of 
litigation, a Supreme Court decision against the IRS and a change in the law by 
Congress last year. 
