<TEXT>
<P>
 Hensel Phelps Construction Co.: The Irvine company has won a $51-million 
contract to build a federal prison in Taft in southwestern Kern County, 
according to the U.S. Bureau of Prisons. 
</P>
<P>
 Hensel Phelps was the low bidder on a project that company spokesman Wayne 
Saxerud says may employ 300 people. 
</P>
<P>
 Saxerud said his company has 21 months to complete the prison. But the bureau 
first must negotiate to have gas and oil lines moved out of the way. 
</P>
<P>
 The prison is expected to house 2,000 minimum-security inmates. 
</P>
