POLICE BLOTTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AZUSA: A 40-year-old store clerk was killed in a robbery Saturday night. Raj 
Kumar Sharma of Covina was working at Michael's Mini Mart at 575 E. Arrow 
Highway when a man burst into the store about 9 p.m. and shot him several times 
in the head and chest. An undetermined amount of cash was stolen. No arrests 
have been made. 
</P>
<P>
 INDUSTRY: Sheriff's deputies responding to a call of a cargo theft about 3:10 
a.m. Friday at a Bullock's warehouse at 16633 Gale Ave. arrived to find a man 
trying to hook up a semi-truck tractor and drive off with $86,736 worth of 
stainless steel kitchenware. Dale Smith, 33, of Los Angeles was arrested after 
he jumped out of the cab and allegedly tried to flee. 
</P>
<P>
 PASADENA: A box of human medical specimens -- including a skull, spinal 
column, collar bone, pelvic bone, femur and a side of ribs -- was stolen from 
the parked car of a medical student in the 2300 block of Dudley Street Saturday 
morning. 
</P>
<P>
 PASADENA: A prowling suspect who was reportedly fleeing police crashed his car 
into another vehicle Sunday night, killing the other driver. Michael Ikeda, 32, 
of Altadena was killed when a car driven by Gerardo Mendoza, 33, of Hawaiian 
Gardens, ran a red light at the intersection of Lake Avenue and Colorado 
Boulevard. Mendoza had been spotted by San Marino police allegedly prowling 
around houses about 10:45 p.m. on San Marino Avenue. He fled north into 
Pasadena along Lake Avenue and police gave pursuit. He has been charged with 
murder. 
</P>
<P>
 POMONA: Police arrested a homicide suspect Feb. 3. Samuel Bernice Williams, 
32, of Ontario was taken into custody without incident in Ontario after 
officers stopped his 1978 Cadillac. Williams is wanted in connection with the 
Jan. 31 slaying of Tom Villanueva Granados, 31, of Pomona, who was found shot 
to death at Holy Cross Cemetery. 
</P>
<P>
 POMONA: Olther Laskey, 24, of Pomona was found shot to death in his home in 
the 1100 block of North Dudley Street on Sunday evening. Several witnesses and 
neighbors have been questioned but no arrests have been made. 
</P>
<P>
 ROWLAND HEIGHTS: The Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department on Wednesday 
opened an Asian Service Center at 18333 E. Colima Road. Five deputies -- fluent 
in Chinese, Korean and Vietnamese -- will be stationed there to provide 
outreach to the Asian community. 
</P>
