<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; MAN ORDERED TO FACE TRIAL IN STABBING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Municipal Court judge on Wednesday ordered an Oxnard man to stand trial on 
murder charges related to the Christmas Day stabbing of his ex-girlfriend's 
son. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Socorro Jimenez, 32, will be arraigned in Superior Court on Feb. 23, said 
Senior Deputy Dist. Atty.Peter D. Kossoris. 
</P>
<P>
 He is accused of stabbing 21-year-old Isaias Guerrero after showing up at the 
home of the victim on Campbell Way in Oxnard about 3 a.m. Dec. 25. 
</P>
<P>
 Before the stabbing, the victim had tried to escort Jimenez off the family's 
property, witnesses said. Jimenez had come to the house and smashed his hand 
against a living-room window. 
</P>
<P>
 He yelled that the victim's mother, 36-year-old Garciela Guerrero, was going 
to pay for breaking off their three-year relationship. DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
