<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ENVIRONMENT: SWIMMERS WARNED OF HAZARDS POSED BY RUNOFF FROM STORM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The environmental group Heal the Bay warns people not to swim in the ocean for 
three days after a storm. 
</P>
<P>
 Rainwater coursing through storm drain pipes carries pollution such as grease, 
pesticides and animal droppings into the ocean, usually elevating the level of 
bacteria along Santa Monica Bay beaches. 
</P>
<P>
 The contaminants, which can cause a variety of health problems, gradually 
dissipate. 
</P>
