<HEADLINE>
<P>
A KIT FOR ALL REASONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONNIE KOENENN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Furniture kits, sold mostly through mail order, come in many ranges of style 
and prices. Here is a sampling. 
</P>
<P>
 * American Bungalow magazine's mail-order Craftsman collection includes two 
kits: the Greene and Greene facsimile fern table of Honduras mahogany and a 
handcrafted redwood miniature bungalow birdhouse. P.O. Box 756, Sierra Madre, 
Calif. 91205-756; (800) 350-3363. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bartley Collection Ltd. specializes in 18th- and 19th-Century reproductions. 
Kits range in price from $29 to $3,400 for more than 300 designs, including 
beds, chests, tables, highboys, dining tables and chairs. Free catalogue. 29060 
Airpark Drive, Easton, Md. 21601; (800) 227-8539. 
</P>
<P>
 * Cohasset Colonials offers reproductions of early American museum pieces in 
pine, cherry and maple. Kits range from $49 to $1,300. Catalogue, $3. 10 
Churchill Road, Hingham, Mass., 02043-1589; (800) 288-2389. 
</P>
<P>
 * Emperor Clock Co. makes kits for grandfather clocks and fine furniture in 
Appalachian oak, Pennsylvania cherry and black walnut. Clock movements are 
brass. Prices range from $200 for a mantel clock kit to $1,895 for a Newbury 
clock with fluted columns. Free catalogue. Emperor Industrial Park, Fairhope, 
Ala. 36532; (800) 642-0011. 
</P>
<P>
 * Wood Classics makes classic mission-style furniture in mahogany, teak, 
cherry and quarter-sawn oak. Free catalogue. P.O. Box 3AB2, Osprey Lane, 
Gardiner, N.Y. 12515; (914) 255-5599. 
</P>
<P>
 * Shaker Shops West manufactures a full-range of kits in domestic rock maple, 
cherry, butternut and quarter-sawn oak. Prices range from a Shaker stand for 
$77 to a cherrywood trestle table for $973. Catalogue, $1.50. P.O. Box 487, 
Inverness, Calif. 94937; (415) 669-7256. 
</P>
<P>
 * Shaker Workshops has Shaker reproductions in maple, cherry and pine, 
including tables, chairs, beds, lamps, mirrors and clocks. Kits range from $40 
to $500. Catalogue, $1. P.O. Box 1028, Concord, Mass. 01742; (617) 646-8985. 
</P>
<P>
 * Yield House furniture kits range from a $49 luggage rack kit to a $749 
armoire. Free catalogue. P.O. Box 2525, Conway, N.H. 03818; (800) 258-4720. 
</P>
<P>
 * Workshop Showcase kits for Shaker and mission-style hardwood furniture range 
from a $75 stool to a $1,100 Shaker picket bed. Catalogue, $2. P.O. Box 500107, 
Austin, Tex. 78750; (512) 331-5470. 
</P>
<P>
 * Coppa Woodworking makes Adirondack outdoor chairs and love seats with wide 
arms and slatted fan backs. Unfinished sugar pine kits range from a $24 
footrest to a $99 love seat. Free brochure. 1231 Paraiso, San Pedro, Calif. 
90731; (310) 548-5332. CONNIE KOENENN 
</P>
</TEXT>
