COMMUNITY NEWS: TORRANCE: CITY COUNCIL SETTLES BIKE ACCIDENT SUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY GUTHRIE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council approved a $100,000 settlement last week with a girl who was 
injured while riding her bicycle on a city sidewalk two years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Michelle Bowman was 7 when she hit a crack in the sidewalk and was thrown over 
the handlebars, fracturing her elbow, said her attorney, Max A. Sauler, who 
handled her lawsuit.The crack in the sidewalk had been pointed out to city 
officials at least two years before the accident, Sauler said. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl, who worked as a model, had to cancel jobs because of her injury and 
will suffer some permanent damage to the range of motion of her elbow, Sauler 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The agreement must still be approved by a judge, but no date for a hearing has 
been set, Sauler said. When the agreement is final, the funds remaining after 
paying medical bills and attorney fees will be put into a trust account for 
Bowman until she turns 18. MARY GUTHRIE 
